    • Method Detail

      • commit

        @Nullable
com.i2rd.cms.bean.contentmodel.CmsModelDataSet commit(PageElement pageElement)
        Commit changes in the UI to the specified PageElement and return a new CmsModelDataSet.

        This is always called after validate(Notifiable) and only if validate returns a "success" value.

        Parameters:
        pageElement - the PageElement to update with changes.
        Returns:
        the new CmsModelDataSet. If isModelDataDirty(EditorUI) returned true then this class should not return null. If isModelDataDirty(EditorUI) returned false it should return null.

      • createUI

        void createUI(EditorUI editorUI)
        Create the UI.

        Initialize the editor and update the UI with MIWT components required by the editor. Don't store the EditorUI for later reference. All work related to the EditorUI or its properties should be done before this method returns. Any work done outside this method on the EditorUI or properties returned from it is undefined and may result in error.

        Parameters:
        editorUI - the EditorUI.

      • destroy

        void destroy()
        Destroy the editor; releasing any resources that have been allocated. This method is guaranteed to be called only once.

      • initialize

        void initialize(PageElement pageElement)
        Initialize the editor for the specified PageElement. This is the first method that is called after instantiation. This method is guaranteed to be called only once.

        After this method call, the PageElement will become detached. If your code needs to access / initialize a proxied property, then it should be done within this method call - Hibernate.initialize(Object). Do not mutate the PageElement here otherwise changes may inadvertantly be saved to the database. Updates to PageElement should be done in commit(PageElement).

        Parameters:
        pageElement - the attached page element.
        See Also:
        Hibernate.initialize(Object)

      • isModelDataDirty

        boolean isModelDataDirty(EditorUI editorUI)
        Return true if the model data is dirty.
        Parameters:
        editorUI - the EditorUI. This should not be stored or referenced outside the scope of the method call.
        Returns:
        true or false.

      • isPageElementDirty

        boolean isPageElementDirty(EditorUI editorUI)
        Return true if the PageElement data is dirty.
        Parameters:
        editorUI - the EditorUI. This should not be stored or referenced outside the scope of the method call.
        Returns:
        true or false.

      • validate

        com.i2rd.cms.editor.ValidationState validate(net.proteusframework.core.notification.Notifiable errors)
        Validate the UI state in preparation for saving changes. This is always called after createUI(EditorUI), isPageElementDirty(EditorUI), and isModelDataDirty(EditorUI).
        Parameters:
        errors - container to add errors for display in the UI.
        Returns:
        the state. If an invalid state is returned, you should set a message in the specified MessageContainer so that the user knows how to correct the situation.
